<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The <a href="/index.php/Paranid" title="Paranid">Paranid</a> <b>Heavy Nemesis</b> is one of the most stylish ships in <i><a href="/index.php/X3:_Terran_Conflict" title="X3: Terran Conflict">X3: Terran Conflict</a></i>, so it would make a good personal yacht for players if not for its tiny cargo bay.  Like the original <a href="/index.php/Nemesis" title="Nemesis">Nemesis</a> it is a highly effective patrol craft.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>This militarized "Heavy" version of the Paranid Nemesis is a no-frills, gritty and very potent corvette.  With ramped-up performance in almost every aspect of the ship, it is the nemesis of almost every opponent.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<p>The Heavy Nemesis addresses the turret problem in the original, with three dual turrets providing almost perfect anti-fighter defense. Its generator is improved, at average level for the heavy corvettes, and it has respectable speed while retaining a low profile, allowing it to easily evade attacks by strafing when player-controlled.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Combat">Combat</span></h2>
<p>Like its predecessor, the Heavy Nemesis can mount the <a href="/index.php/Ion_Shard_Railgun" title="Ion Shard Railgun">Ion Shard Railgun</a>, but still has insufficient power to justify the weapon's use.  It can still severely lower the energy available to some battleships or <a href="/index.php/TL" title="TL">TLs</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment">Equipment</span></h2>
<p>Like many <a href="/index.php/M6%2B" title="M6+">M6+</a> craft, the Heavy Nemesis mounts <a href="/index.php/Shields#200_MJ" title="Shields">4x200MJ</a> shields, making it quite difficult to destroy using low-key weapons.  It can use a wide variety of weapons, usually <a href="/index.php/High_Energy_Plasma_Thrower" title="High Energy Plasma Thrower">High Energy Plasma Throwers</a>, <a href="/index.php/Ion_Shard_Railgun" title="Ion Shard Railgun">Ion Shard Railguns</a> or <a href="/index.php/Concussion_Impulse_Generator" title="Concussion Impulse Generator">Concussion Impulse Generators</a> on its fixed mounts, and assorted light armaments in the turrets, such as the <a href="/index.php/Particle_Accelerator_Cannon" title="Particle Accelerator Cannon">Particle Accelerator Cannon</a> or <a href="/index.php/Pulsed_Beam_Emitter" title="Pulsed Beam Emitter">Pulsed Beam Emitter</a>.
</p>
